Tulsa - Creator CRM System
In recognition of Roy and Leon Daley
***Project Overview
Tulsa is a comprehensive, legitimate creator relationship management (CRM) system designed to help content creators manage their subscriber relationships professionally and ethically. Built with Rust for performance and reliability, Tulsa provides a complete solution for tracking subscribers, managing interactions, and maintaining authentic engagement with your audience.
What Makes Tulsa Different
Unlike deceptive automation tools, Tulsa focuses on empowering human creators to:
Manage relationships more efficiently
Track engagement patterns transparently
Make informed business decisions
Maintain authentic connections with subscribers
Core Components
1. Web-Based GUI
A beautiful, modern interface featuring:
Dashboard: Real-time analytics and statistics
Subscriber Management: Complete subscriber profiles with filtering
Interaction Tracking: Record and view all interactions
Expiring Alerts: Monitor subscriptions needing renewal
2. REST API
Full-featured API for:
CRUD operations on subscribers
Interaction logging
Analytics and reporting
Custom integrations
3. Command-Line Interface (CLI)
Bash-based tool for quick operations:
Add and manage subscribers
Record interactions
View statistics
Filter and search
4. Database Layer
SQLite-based storage with:
Subscriber profiles with rich metadata
Interaction history
Automated tier tracking
Subscription expiration monitoring
Technology Stack
Backend: Rust with Axum web framework
Database: SQLite with SQLx
Frontend: Pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no frameworks)
API: RESTful JSON API
CLI: Bash scripting
Key Features
Subscriber Management
Store comprehensive subscriber information
Track username, platform, tier, and preferences
Add personal notes and birthday information
Filter by platform and tier
Interaction Tracking
Record messages, purchases, tips, and renewals
Automatic spending total calculation
Complete interaction history per subscriber
Timestamp all activities
Analytics Dashboard
Total subscriber count by tier (VIP, Regular, Casual)
Total revenue tracking
Expiring subscription alerts (7/14/30 day windows)
Real-time statistics
Tier System
VIP: High-value subscribers ($500+ lifetime)
Regular: Active, moderate engagement
Casual: Infrequent or trial subscribers
Ethical Design Principles
Transparency: No deceptive automation
Human-Centered: Creator remains in control
Data Privacy: All data stored locally
Legitimate Use: Designed for authentic relationship management
No Platform Violations: Complies with all platform terms of service
Architecture
creator_crm/
├── src/
│   ├── main.rs          # Server initialization and routing
│   ├── models.rs        # Data structures
│   ├── db.rs            # Database operations
│   └── handlers.rs      # API endpoints
├── static/
│   ├── index.html       # Web GUI
│   ├── styles.css       # Styling
│   └── app.js           # Frontend logic
├── crm_cli.sh           # Command-line tool
├── start.sh             # Quick start script
└── creator_crm.db       # SQLite database (generated)
Use Cases
Daily Management: Track interactions as they happen
Revenue Insights: Monitor total spending and tier progression
Renewal Management: Identify expiring subscriptions proactively
Relationship Building: Store preferences and personalization data
Business Analytics: Understand subscriber base composition
Security & Privacy
Local Storage: All data remains on your machine
No Cloud Services: No third-party data sharing
No Platform Access: Doesn't connect to any social platforms
Manual Operation: Human reviews and approves all actions
